@startuml sequence-ai-chat
!theme vibrant
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam participantBorderColor #6366F1
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #DBEAFE
skinparam actorBorderColor #1D4ED8
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #CBD5E1
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFBEB
skinparam noteBorderColor #F59E0B
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam defaultFontColor #111827
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceParticipantFontColor #111827
skinparam sequenceActorFontColor #111827
skinparam sequenceMessageFontColor #111827
skinparam sequenceGroupFontColor #111827
skinparam noteFontColor #111827

title Council Permit Portal — How the AI Chat Works

actor "User\n(Any role)" as U #DBEAFE
participant "Chat\nScreen"      as UI #E0E7FF
participant "System\n(Server + Database)" as SYS #EDE9FE
participant "AI\n(Groq / Gemini)" as AI #FEF3C7

' ─── OPEN CHAT ───────────────────────────────────────────────
U -> UI  : Opens the AI Chat page
UI -> SYS : Loads previous conversations
SYS --> UI : Past conversations shown in the sidebar

alt Starting a new conversation
  U -> UI : Clicks "New Chat"
else Continuing an old one
  U -> UI : Clicks a conversation in the sidebar
  UI -> SYS : Loads the messages for that conversation
  SYS --> UI : Previous messages appear on screen
end

' ─── SEND A MESSAGE ──────────────────────────────────────────
U -> UI  : Types a question and presses Enter
UI -> SYS : Sends the message along with conversation history

SYS -> SYS : Reads the message and figures out what the user needs
note right
  Examples of what it detects:
  · "Which permit do I need?" → recommend a permit
  · "What documents do I need?" → list required documents
  · "How does the process work?" → explain the steps
  · "Show my applications" → fetch user's own records
  · General question → just answer it
end note

' ─── LOOK UP THE RIGHT INFORMATION ──────────────────────────
alt User needs a permit recommendation
  SYS -> SYS : Looks up all available permit types
  SYS -> SYS : Matches keywords from the message to real scenarios

else User is asking about required documents
  SYS -> SYS : Detects which permit type was mentioned in the conversation
  SYS -> SYS : Looks up the document requirements for that permit

else User is asking how the process works
  SYS -> SYS : Detects which permit type was mentioned
  alt Permit type identified
    SYS -> SYS : Looks up the steps and required documents for that permit
  else No permit type mentioned yet
    SYS -> SYS : Loads all permit names to show as quick-reply buttons
    note right: Asks one short question — "Which permit are you applying for?"
  end

else User wants to see their own applications
  SYS -> SYS : Looks up the user's submitted applications and their statuses

else General question or greeting
  note right: No data lookup needed — AI answers directly
end

' ─── ASK THE AI ──────────────────────────────────────────────
SYS -> AI  : Sends the question together with the looked-up data\nand instructions on how to respond
AI --> SYS : Writes a clear, formatted answer

' ─── SAVE AND SEND BACK ──────────────────────────────────────
SYS -> SYS : Saves the conversation so it can be resumed later
SYS -> SYS : Checks if the AI included quick-reply suggestions in the answer
SYS --> UI : Sends back the response, any quick-reply buttons,\nany charts, and any action buttons

' ─── SHOW THE ANSWER ─────────────────────────────────────────
UI --> U : Displays the formatted answer (bold, lists, etc.)

alt Quick-reply buttons are available
  UI --> U : Shows clickable buttons (e.g. permit names, "Other")
  U -> UI  : Clicks a button — sends it as the next message automatically
end

alt A chart or table was generated
  UI --> U : Shows a bar chart, pie chart, or data table
end

alt An action button was included
  UI --> U : Shows a card like "Start a New Application"
end

@enduml
